# M5 Lesson Layout & Spacing

Apply to all four lessons under `fullstack-mastery-module-5-server-state-with-tanstack-query/` (`0`–`3`). Same spacing contract as M6 — **UI unchanged**, spacing only.

## Spacing tokens (only these)

| Token | Use |
|-------|-----|
| **`p-3`** | **Only** on `<main>` in `App.tsx` |
| **`gap-3`** | Between structural blocks (form fields, list rows, feed sections, avatar ↔ text column) |
| **`h-3`** | Small spacer: title → description; in-route nav (link → content on L0 `/users`) |
| **`h-6`** | Large spacer: description → lesson body; **action/form block → user list/feed block** |
| **`mt-3`** | Optional section margin (stepper, status bar) |

Do **not** use `gap-1/2/4`, `px-2 py-2`, `p-6`, `mb-*`, or extra padding in `globals.css` on `main`.

## globals.css

`main` may set `max-width` + `margin: 0 auto` only — **no `padding`**. Outer page padding comes solely from `p-3` on `<main>` in `App.tsx`.

## Functional blocks

- **Block A — actions/form**: Refetch button, AddUserForm, NameEditor, etc. **No Card** wrapper.
- **Block B — data list/feed**: User ListBox, infinite scroll feed. Separated from Block A by `<div className="h-6" />`.
- **Within Block B**: list items spaced with `gap-3` on `ListBox`, **no item padding**.

## Text stack (no gap)

Name + email under avatar → `flex flex-col` without `gap-*`.

## ListBox pattern (all lessons)

```tsx
<ListBox className="gap-3 p-0" …>
  <ListBox.Item className="rounded-none p-0 …">
```

Skeleton rows: `flex flex-col gap-3`; row inner text placeholders without `gap-1.5`.

## App.tsx shell

```tsx
<main className="min-h-screen bg-background p-3">
  <div className="mx-auto max-w-2xl">
    … title …
    <div className="h-3" />
    … description …
    <div className="h-6" />
    {content}
  </div>
</main>
```

## L3 infinite feed

Status bar + scroll area → wrap in `flex flex-col gap-3` (same functional block). Do not use `h-6` between status and list.

## Forms

- `form className="flex flex-col gap-3"`
- Submit button direct child of form (no extra wrapper div)
- No `gap-1` on `TextField` wrappers
